Sentencas: The influence of titanium doping level in Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-delta (BSCT) oxides on their phase structure, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), and single-cell performance with BSCT cathodes has been investigated.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The incorporation of Ti can lead to the phase transition of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-delta from hexagonal to cubic structure.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The solid solution limitation of Ti in Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-delta is 0.15-0.3 under 1100 C BSCT shows a small polaron conduction behavior and the electrical conductivity increases steadily in the testing temperature range (300-900 C), leading to a relatively high conductivity at high temperatures.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity decreases with increasing Ti content.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The addition of Ti deteriorates the cathode performance of BSCT slightly but decreases theTECsignificantly.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The TEC of BSCT is about 14 x 10 (6) K (1),which results in a good physical compatibility of BSCT with Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (GDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: BSCT also shows excellent thermal cyclic stability of electrical conductivity and good chemical stability with GDC.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: These properties make BSCT a promising cathode candidate for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical studies of Ba0.6Sr0.4Co1-yTiyO3-δ as a new cathode material for IT-SOFCs
